%N A392834 Time taken to get n people from one side of a bridge to the other where (a) the only flashlight must be carried when crossing; (b) at most three people may cross at the same time; (c) a group crosses at the speed of the slowest member; and (d) the k-th person requires k seconds to cross the bridge.
%C A392834 The optimal strategy can be described as follows. Send 3 fastest (1, 2, 3), then the fastest back (1), then the 3 slowest (n, n-1, n-2), then the fastest back (2). Thereafter, send the 3 slowest (n-3, n-4, n-5), then the fastest back (3), so that the current state is of the form {1,...,n-6}, which allows us to obtain a recurrence relation of order 6.
%H A392834 <a href="/index/Rec#order_06">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (1,1,0,-1,-1,1).
%F A392834 a(n) = n^2/6 + 2*n - 181/36 + (-1)^n/4 - 2/9 * cos(2*n*Pi/3) for n >= 7.
%F A392834 a(n) = a(n-6) + 2n + 6 for n >= 13, with initial conditions a(7) = 17, a(8) = 22, a(9) = 26, a(10) = 32, a(11) = 37, a(12) = 43.
